1. simple Java program to reverse every alternate word in the string while preserving spaces and word order.
i/p: "i am a qa engineer"
o/p: "i ma a aq engineer"

public class ReverseAlternateWords {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String s = "i am a qa engineer";
        String result = reverseAlternateWords(s);
        System.out.println("Original: " + s);
        System.out.println("Output  : " + result);
    }

    public static String reverseAlternateWords(String str) {
        String[] words = str.split(" ");
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            // Reverse alternate words (2nd, 4th, etc.)
            if (i % 2 == 1) {
                result.append(new StringBuilder(words[i]).reverse());
            } else {
                result.append(words[i]);
            }

            // Add space except after last word
            if (i < words.length - 1) {
                result.append(" ");
            }
        }

        return result.toString();
    }
}

Q:2 --  WAP sum of the least numbers from the array, and numbers can be duplicate.
arr[] = {3, 5, 2, 3, 7, 2}
op- 4

import java.util.Arrays;

public class SumOfLeastNumbers {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {3, 5, 2, 3, 7, 2};

        // Sort the array
        Arrays.sort(arr);

        // Sum of two smallest numbers
        int sum = arr[0] + arr[1];

        System.out.println("Sum of least numbers: " + sum);
    }
}

without sorting
public class SumOfLeastNumbers {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {3, 5, 2, 3, 7, 2};

        int min1 = arr[0];
        int min2 = arr[1];

        // Ensure min1 is smaller than min2 initially
        if (min1 > min2) {
            int temp = min1;
            min1 = min2;
            min2 = temp;
        }

        for (int i = 2; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < min1) {
                min2 = min1;
                min1 = arr[i];
            } else if (arr[i] < min2) {
                min2 = arr[i];
            }
        }

        int sum = min1 + min2;
        System.out.println("Sum of least numbers: " + sum);
    }
}

